The vote is part of the last of three stages of elections for the People’s Assembly, the parliament’s lower house. Each voting stage involves polling in nine governorates (out of total 27 governorates). According to Egypt’s elections law, two-thirds of the parliamentary seats will be allocated through party list races, while one-third of the seats are allocated through concurrent single-winner races. After each initial vote, run-off elections are held a week later between front-runners in single-winner races where none of the candidates got 50%+ of the total vote.
